===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|linguistic morphology}} A smallest [[linguistic]] unit within a word that can carry a [[meaning]], such as "un-", "break", and "-able" in the word "unbreakable".
#: The word ''[[pigs]]'' consists of two '''morphemes''': ''pig'' (a particular animal) and ''s'' (indication of the plural).''
#: The word ''[[werewolves|werewolves']]'' consists of four morphemes: "''were''" (~ man), "''wolf''" (a particular animal), "''es''" (plural), and " ' " (indicating possessive).

